Kryon: Plan 9 Window Manager

A Plan 9-style window manager using bind mount namespaces for per-window
isolation. Kryon provides a desktop environment following Plan 9's philosophy
of separating the display server from window management.

OVERVIEW

Kryon is a window manager that uses Marrow as the display server and implements
rio-style namespaces where each window can have its own isolated /dev devices
through bind mounts.

Architecture:

    Marrow (Display Server)
        ├── /dev/screen     - Main framebuffer
        ├── /dev/cons       - Console
        ├── /dev/mouse      - Mouse input
        └── /dev/kbd        - Keyboard input

    Kryon (Window Manager)
        ├── Manages windows
        ├── Builds per-window namespaces
        └── Uses bind mounts for device isolation

Each window gets its own namespace where /dev/screen points to that window's
virtual devices through bind mounts, just like Plan 9's rio.

QUICK START

Build and run:

    nix-shell --run "make clean && make"

Start Marrow (display server):

    ./marrow --port 17011

Start Kryon:

    ./bin/kryon --example minimal

Or run components separately:

    # Terminal 1: Display viewer (emu)
    ../emu/bin/emu

    # Terminal 2: Window manager
    ./bin/kryon --example minimal

DOCUMENTATION

See examples/ directory for UI definition examples.

COMPONENTS

bin/kryon            - Window manager
bin/tjk              - CLI tool
examples/            - UI definition examples

Note: The display client (emu) is now in ../emu/

REQUIREMENTS

    - Nix (for dependency management)
    - Marrow (display server)
    - SDL2 (graphics backend)

BUILD

    nix-shell --run "make clean && make"     - Build with Nix
    nix-shell --run "make"                   - Build
    nix-shell --run "make clean"             - Clean build artifacts

Binary: bin/kryon (window manager), bin/tjk (CLI tool)

CONFIGURATION

Command-line options:

    --example NAME        Load an example from examples/
    --load FILE.kryon     Load a specific file
    --blank               Show blank screen
    --list-examples       List available examples
    --help                Show help message

EXAMPLES

Create a simple window:

    demo "Demo Window" 800x600 {
        absolute {
            button btn_click "Click Me" {
                x: 50
                y: 50
                width: 200
                height: 40
            }
            label lbl_hello "Hello, World!" {
                x: 50
                y: 120
            }
        }
    }

List services:

    ./bin/kryon --list-examples
